          <div id="FITB_575" class="FITB formRender">
            <p>Treatment contract<br /><br />General requirements for completion of ABS court ordered programs:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>
                <span style="background-color:transparent">
                  1- Total abstinence from all drugs and alcohol.
                </span>
              </li>
              <li>
                <span style="background-color:transparent">
                  2- Total compliance with program attendance and punctuality policies.
                </span>
              </li>
              <li>
                <span style="background-color:transparent">
                  3- Maximum participation in all therapy sessions.
                </span>
              </li>
              <li>
                <span style="background-color:transparent">
                  4- Completion of all homework assignments.
                </span>
              </li>
              <li>
                <span style="background-color:transparent">
                  5- Total compliance with financial responsibilities.
                </span>
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p><br /><span style="background-color:transparent">Financial Responsibilities: Clients are to pay all fees before sessions start. Clients who violate this policy will not be seen and will be marked absent.</span><br /><br /><span style="background-color:transparent">Attendance Policy: Clients are responsible for attending every scheduled session. Clients who are absent for sessions will be responsible for payment of that session and have to make it up. If you acquire more than three unexcused absences you will be discharged from the program for non-compliance and referred back to the court or other supervising agencies. You may be given a chance to re-enter the program but you will be required to start the program from the beginning. The only excused absence is if you go to ABSRehabilitation.com Request to be excused tab and submit your request no less than 12 hours before the scheduled appointment. Send this message including your full name with a valid excuse. You will be excused and expected to return to the program during your next scheduled session and your absence must be verified with documentation.</span><br /><br /><span style="background-color:transparent">Punctuality Policy: Clients are responsible for arriving to their appointment on time. All lateness will be counted as an unexcused absence.</span></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="form-line" data-type="control_inline" id="id_581">
        <div id="cid_581" class="form-input-wide jf-required">
          <div id="FITB_581" class="FITB formRender">
            <p>Drug Testing Policy: I am aware that if I am under court order to attend Applied Behavioral Sciences as part of my treatment I may be asked to void supervised urine specimens periodically throughout my treatment. I am aware that if I am under court order and refuse to submit to this may result in being terminated from the program. <br /><br />Progress Reporting: I am aware that I must keep track of all my court appearances and legal hearings and must request a progress report from the program no less than one week in advance to prepare for my hearing. <span style="color:#555555;background-color:transparent">The only accepted request for documentation should be made at ABSRehabilitation.com Documentation Request TAB and submit your request for a progress report. I am aware that I will be required to pay a fee if I do not request documentation prior to one week of your hearing and if I need a progress report in less then one week time I must make an Expedited Documentation Request at ABSRehabilitation.com. </span><br /><br /><span id="id_581_signature-1" data-type="signaturebox" class="FITB-inptCont"><input type="hidden" name="q581_input581[signature-1]" id="581_input_signature-1" class=" validate[required]" /><span class="FITB-sign-button" tabindex="0" role="button" aria-label="E-Signature Field"><img alt class="FITB-sign-image" /></span><label for="581_input_signature-1">Signature</label><span class="form-required">*</span></span>   </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </li>
